pauper (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Improve phone-sized GTK layout by reducing window width requirements,
    left-aligning the main title, stacking card actions, tightening settings
    controls, and moving status/retry messages to the bottom of the screen.
  * Restore labelled voice action buttons and keep the unload action below the
    current memory status with a clearer icon.
  * Hide speaker details in status text for single-speaker voices.
  * Create the default TOML configuration file on first run when it is missing.
  * Prefer system ONNX Runtime over Pauper's private Piper target path to avoid
    duplicate ONNX schema registration errors.
  * Block the separate Python onnx package in the daemon and remove stale
    private onnx and onnxruntime installs during package configuration.
  * Format CLI voice status without redundant speaker details for
    single-speaker voices.
  * Update AppStream release metadata for 0.1.1.

 -- pauper contributors <noreply@example.invalid>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 04:15:00 +1200

